  <div class='medium-8 columns'><div class="webex-group">
<div class="webex-question">
<div class="webex-check webex-box">
<p>The following figure shows a scatterplot. Which of the following statements are correct?</p>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," /></p>
<div id="webex-30f6a6dc3bc3f9ba9f724489f60d26ae" class="webex-checkboxgroup" data-answer="aABKBk0GSFIfUz4=">
<label><input type='checkbox' autocomplete='off' name='30f6a6dc3bc3f9ba9f724489f60d26ae'/><span>The absolute value of the correlation coefficient is at least <span class="math inline">\(0.8\)</span>.</span></label><label><input type='checkbox' autocomplete='off' name='30f6a6dc3bc3f9ba9f724489f60d26ae'/><span>The slope of the regression line is about <span class="math inline">\(1\)</span>.</span></label><label><input type='checkbox' autocomplete='off' name='30f6a6dc3bc3f9ba9f724489f60d26ae'/><span>The standard deviation of <span class="math inline">\(Y\)</span> is at least <span class="math inline">\(6\)</span>.</span></label><label><input type='checkbox' autocomplete='off' name='30f6a6dc3bc3f9ba9f724489f60d26ae'/><span>For <span class="math inline">\(X = 0.3\)</span>, <span class="math inline">\(Y\)</span> can be expected to be about <span class="math inline">\(0\)</span>.</span></label><label><input type='checkbox' autocomplete='off' name='30f6a6dc3bc3f9ba9f724489f60d26ae'/><span>The mean of <span class="math inline">\(X\)</span> is at most <span class="math inline">\(5\)</span>.</span></label>
</div>
</div>
<div class="webex-solution">
<ul>
<li>False. No association between the variables is observed in the scatterplot. This implies a correlation coefficient close to <span class="math inline">\(0\)</span>.</li>
<li>False. The slope of the regression line is given by <span class="math inline">\(r \cdot s_y/s_x\)</span> and hence not about equal to <span class="math inline">\(1\)</span>.</li>
<li>False. The standard deviation of <span class="math inline">\(Y\)</span> is about equal to <span class="math inline">\(1\)</span> and is therefore smaller than <span class="math inline">\(6\)</span>.</li>
<li>True. The regression line at <span class="math inline">\(X=0.3\)</span> implies a value of about <span class="math inline">\(Y = 0\)</span>.</li>
<li>True. The mean of <span class="math inline">\(X\)</span> is about equal to <span class="math inline">\(0\)</span> and hence is smaller than <span class="math inline">\(5\)</span>.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div class="webex-question">
<div class="webex-check webex-box">
<p>The following figure shows a scatterplot. Which of the following statements are correct?</p>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," /></p>
<div id="webex-58d159b57727ccddae0bc52624cb056e" class="webex-checkboxgroup" data-answer="bghIARkJTgUbBm8=">
<label><input type='checkbox' autocomplete='off' name='58d159b57727ccddae0bc52624cb056e'/><span>The slope of the regression line is about <span class="math inline">\(1\)</span>.</span></label><label><input type='checkbox' autocomplete='off' name='58d159b57727ccddae0bc52624cb056e'/><span>For <span class="math inline">\(X = -0.3\)</span>, <span class="math inline">\(Y\)</span> can be expected to be about <span class="math inline">\(1.9\)</span>.</span></label><label><input type='checkbox' autocomplete='off' name='58d159b57727ccddae0bc52624cb056e'/><span>The mean of <span class="math inline">\(Y\)</span> is at least <span class="math inline">\(30\)</span>.</span></label><label><input type='checkbox' autocomplete='off' name='58d159b57727ccddae0bc52624cb056e'/><span>The standard deviation of <span class="math inline">\(Y\)</span> is at least <span class="math inline">\(6\)</span>.</span></label><label><input type='checkbox' autocomplete='off' name='58d159b57727ccddae0bc52624cb056e'/><span>The absolute value of the correlation coefficient is at most <span class="math inline">\(0.8\)</span>.</span></label>
</div>
</div>
<div class="webex-solution">
<ul>
<li>False. The slope of the regression line is given by <span class="math inline">\(r \cdot s_y/s_x\)</span> and hence not about equal to <span class="math inline">\(1\)</span>.</li>
<li>False. The regression line at <span class="math inline">\(X=-0.3\)</span> implies a value of about <span class="math inline">\(Y = -0.1\)</span>.</li>
<li>False. The mean of <span class="math inline">\(Y\)</span> is about equal to <span class="math inline">\(0\)</span> and hence is smaller than <span class="math inline">\(30\)</span>.</li>
<li>False. The standard deviation of <span class="math inline">\(Y\)</span> is about equal to <span class="math inline">\(1\)</span> and is therefore smaller than <span class="math inline">\(6\)</span>.</li>
<li>True. Only a slightly positive association between the variables is observable in the scatterplot. This implies a correlation coefficient with an absolute value smaller than <span class="math inline">\(0.8\)</span>.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div class="webex-question">
<div class="webex-check webex-box">
<p>The following figure shows a scatterplot. Which of the following statements are correct?</p>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," /></p>
<div id="webex-55f7a3a35a2e334e85cf8cbf14dec0d2" class="webex-checkboxgroup" data-answer="bgVKBk0DTQIZUW8=">
<label><input type='checkbox' autocomplete='off' name='55f7a3a35a2e334e85cf8cbf14dec0d2'/><span>The standard deviation of <span class="math inline">\(X\)</span> is at least <span class="math inline">\(6\)</span>.</span></label><label><input type='checkbox' autocomplete='off' name='55f7a3a35a2e334e85cf8cbf14dec0d2'/><span>The scatterplot is standardized.</span></label><label><input type='checkbox' autocomplete='off' name='55f7a3a35a2e334e85cf8cbf14dec0d2'/><span>For <span class="math inline">\(X = -0.6\)</span>, <span class="math inline">\(Y\)</span> can be expected to be about <span class="math inline">\(1.4\)</span>.</span></label><label><input type='checkbox' autocomplete='off' name='55f7a3a35a2e334e85cf8cbf14dec0d2'/><span>The mean of <span class="math inline">\(X\)</span> is at most <span class="math inline">\(5\)</span>.</span></label><label><input type='checkbox' autocomplete='off' name='55f7a3a35a2e334e85cf8cbf14dec0d2'/><span>The absolute value of the correlation coefficient is at most <span class="math inline">\(0.8\)</span>.</span></label>
</div>
</div>
<div class="webex-solution">
<ul>
<li>False. The standard deviation of <span class="math inline">\(X\)</span> is about equal to <span class="math inline">\(1\)</span> and is therefore smaller than <span class="math inline">\(6\)</span>.</li>
<li>True. <span class="math inline">\(X\)</span> and <span class="math inline">\(Y\)</span> have both mean <span class="math inline">\(0\)</span> and variance <span class="math inline">\(1\)</span>.</li>
<li>False. The regression line at <span class="math inline">\(X=-0.6\)</span> implies a value of about <span class="math inline">\(Y = -0.6\)</span>.</li>
<li>True. The mean of <span class="math inline">\(X\)</span> is about equal to <span class="math inline">\(0\)</span> and hence is smaller than <span class="math inline">\(5\)</span>.</li>
<li>False. A strong association between the variables is given in the scatterplot. Hence the absolute value of the correlation coefficient is close to <span class="math inline">\(1\)</span> and therefore larger than <span class="math inline">\(0.8\)</span>.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div></div>
</div>

<div class='row t20 b1'>
  <div class='medium-4 columns'><b>Description:</b></div>
  <div class='medium-8 columns'>Scatterplot in an (x, y) regression setup needs to be interpreted regarding location/spread of the marginal distributions, the correlation in the joint distribution, and the corresponding regression slope. Data are drawn randomly from a suitable data-generating process so that each multiple-choice item is either about correct or clearly wrong.</div>
